Durban - The details surrounding the death of a 22-year-old Hillcrest woman who was assaulted and killed on Wednesday morning are sketchy. The incident took place at a home in Winston Park. ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said paramedics arrived on scene and found the woman lying on the floor in a pool of blood. "Paramedics assessed the woman and found that she had sustained a serious head wound." He said she showed no signs of life. "Unfortunately, nothing could be done for her and she was declared dead on scene," said Meiring. He added that it is believed the woman was hit on the head with a brick. SAPS were on scene. Details leading up to the incident are unknown at this stage. When contacted for comment, KZN spokesman Colonel Thembeka Mbhele,said the crime scene was still active. This is developing story. Updates to follow. DAILY NEWS